I'm still a little trash. I guess you get it from your dad.

225
00:18:50.280 --> 00:18:52.280
Ha ha ha ha ha!

226
00:19:01.720 --> 00:19:05.000
Right on time. This food truck is very fuzzy.

227
00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:07.640
Yeah, there's even that staggering old man they mentioned.

228
00:19:07.640 --> 00:19:09.400
Jesus. Wow.

229
00:19:09.400 --> 00:19:14.440
You put us through all that just to help a burnt out restaurant staff start a food truck? Basic.

230
00:19:15.000 --> 00:19:17.000
She is more complex than that.

231
00:19:17.960 --> 00:19:20.440
Damn. Great dog.

232
00:19:20.440 --> 00:19:22.440
That's better than avocado toast.

233
00:19:22.440 --> 00:19:24.440
You don't get new ones.

234
00:19:24.440 --> 00:19:28.440
You sure you cogs don't want to keep hanging out? Was it ever real?

235
00:19:28.440 --> 00:19:32.440
Rick Sanchez doesn't want to hear the answer to that.

236
00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:35.400
But if he did...

237
00:19:39.400 --> 00:19:44.120
I tried the portal again. Oh, dice. Rick really hates the goonies.

238
00:19:44.200 --> 00:19:49.400
I think we're going to like it in Garbtopia. In fact, I've taken a trash wife.

239
00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:51.640
You've taken her?

240
00:19:51.640 --> 00:19:57.400
We gave ourselves to each other. I'd stay down here even if there was a way out.

241
00:19:57.400 --> 00:20:00.040
They won't be able to make you pay child support down here, huh?

242
00:20:01.080 --> 00:20:05.800
Oh, dad. Look at the two of us spending time together.

243
00:20:05.800 --> 00:20:07.800
Yeah, this is nice.

244
00:20:07.960 --> 00:20:15.320
Is that a food truck? We're already gentrifying.

245
00:20:15.320 --> 00:20:18.760
Rick! Rick! Rick! Get me out of here! Oh, God!

246
00:20:18.760 --> 00:20:21.640
Don't worry. Our son won't be like him.

247
00:20:21.640 --> 00:20:25.000
It's nothing personal. I'm only 14. I gotta get out of here.

248
00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:29.960
That was the last time I saw my father. Once more, my mother's voice came to me.

249
00:20:29.960 --> 00:20:33.480
Carried on the wind. Be free, my son.

250
00:20:34.200 --> 00:20:40.200
And somehow I did feel free. My father was horrible. And my mother was garbage.

251
00:20:40.760 --> 00:20:45.000
But I knew myself now. And somehow that was enough.

252
00:20:46.680 --> 00:20:47.400
Told you.

253
00:20:47.400 --> 00:20:48.840
That little shit.

254
00:20:48.840 --> 00:20:51.640
Can't believe he got a book deal on Rick's trash moon.

255
00:20:51.640 --> 00:20:53.960
Come on, reporting. You guys still read books?

256
00:21:03.480 --> 00:21:05.480
Oh, my God.

257
00:21:28.440 --> 00:21:31.320
Order 53. Hot cogs. Chicago style.

258
00:21:32.040 --> 00:21:37.960
Uh, if I may. I know there's zero substitutions, but I would never want onions in my hot dog.

259
00:21:37.960 --> 00:21:39.000
Yes, you do.

260
00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:40.680
Uh, if I may, I do not.

261
00:21:40.680 --> 00:21:43.720
You die of a massive coronary at the age of 43.

262
00:21:44.280 --> 00:21:49.720
Uh, if... if... if I may.

263
00:21:50.280 --> 00:21:51.960
Boss wants to see you.

264
00:21:51.960 --> 00:21:53.720
Is that a prediction or...?

265
00:21:53.720 --> 00:21:55.240
Just go talk to him, Steve.

266
00:21:57.160 --> 00:21:57.960
Did you get any of that?

